[[File:Star_Wars_Blog.png|frame|''Star Wars'' Blog logo]]
The '''''Star Wars'' Blog''' was the official [[Wikipedia:blog|blog]] on [[StarWars.com]]. It has since been merged into the official site's "News + Blog" section, with most posts being re-published as articles. The last blog post was made on [[June 24]], [[2014]] with the blog shutting down shortly thereafter. The subdomain now redirects to the News section on [[StarWars.com]].

It featured contributions by [[Albin Johnson]], [[Ashley Eckstein]], [[Jenn Fujikawa]], [[Bryan Young]], [[Casey Pugh]], [[Dave Filoni]], [[Jennifer Landa]], [[Jonathan W. Rinzler]], [[Katie Cook]], [[Leland Chee]], [[Mary Franklin]], [[Pablo Hidalgo]], [[Pete Vilmur]], [[Stephen J. Sansweet]], and the StarWars.com Team.

It replaced the [[Star Wars: Blogs]] prior to the [[2011]] website revamp, where multiple users could create their own blogs on StarWars.com.

Starting on [[September 9]], [[2013]], the blog began running a top-ten list called "The StarWars.com Ten," which involves the top ten aspects of a category of ''Star Wars'' chosen by the blog's staff. The first top-ten list featured lightsaber duels and the second featured starfighters.

